File: Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize has announced that as of Saturday, the number of confirmed COVID-19 in South Africa is 3,034. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 5647. This is an increase of 297 cases from Wednesday. Minister of Health Dr Zwelini Mkhize said in a statement on Thursday that the total number of tests conducted to date is 207,530 of which 10,403 were done in the last 24 hours.  Statement 30 April 2020 (2) by Travis Richards on Scribd  Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.